{
  "texts": [
    "The outcome of a deterministic model is therefore always the same (like a calculator).",
    "As a result, GenAIs are not just (un)surprisingly bad at math but are unpredictable and inconsistent: they vary each time they generate content [2].So, what does this mean for the content it creates?",
    "Worryingly, this means that it can produce text that feels coherent but lacks factual or logical accuracy (i.e.",
    "it can contain made-up information), as it merely determines the probability of certain words occurring after one another.",
    "Dan Lametti describes this in his webinar on AI and Academia [15] as the lack of editing, fact checking and refinement."
  ]
}